{"DAB":[{"def":"A skillful hand; a dabster; an expert.","pos":""}],"DABB":[{"def":"A large, spine-tailed lizard (Uromastix spinipes), found in Egypt, Arabia, and Palestine; -- called also dhobb, and dhabb.","pos":""}],"DABBER":[{"def":"That with which one dabs; hence, a pad or other device used by printers, engravers, etc.","pos":""}],"DABBLE":[{"def":"To wet by little dips or strokes; to spatter; to sprinkle; to moisten; to wet.","pos":""}],"DABBLER":[{"def":"One who dabbles.","pos":""},{"def":"One who dips slightly into anything; a superficial meddler.","pos":""}],"DABBLINGLY":[{"def":"In a dabbling manner.","pos":""}],"DABCHICK":[{"def":"A small water bird (Podilymbus podiceps), allied to the grebes, remarkable for its quickness in diving; -- called also dapchick, dobchick, dipchick, didapper, dobber, devil-diver, hell-diver, and pied-billed grebe.","pos":""}],"DABOIA":[{"def":"A large and highly venomous Asiatic viper (Daboia xanthica).","pos":""}],"DABSTER":[{"def":"One who is skilled; a master of his business; a proficient; an adept.","pos":""}]}